00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:47.200
Number 10: Eye Contact.

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:52.500
Eye contact is key when it comes to desmonstrating your attraction to another person.

00:00:52.560 --> 00:00:56.080
When we make eye contact with a prospective partner,

00:00:56.080 --> 00:00:59.800
we are actually searching for evidence of their attraction to us

00:00:59.860 --> 00:01:04.120
through the psychological response of pupil dilation.

00:01:04.120 --> 00:01:10.220
This is also why staring into one another's eyes can often feels so intimate.

00:01:10.220 --> 00:01:14.920
Therefore, one of the best ways to let someone know you're interested in them

00:01:14.960 --> 00:01:21.380
is to gave into their big brown, blue or green eyes.

00:01:21.460 --> 00:01:24.620
Number 9: Wear red.

00:01:24.660 --> 00:01:30.540
Not only is red an eye catching color that flatters many different skin tones,

00:01:30.600 --> 00:01:34.340
red is also a symbol of lust and sexuality.

00:01:34.400 --> 00:01:38.760
with studies showing that, when both men and women wear red,

00:01:38.860 --> 00:01:42.140
they appear more attractive to the opposite sex.

00:01:42.380 --> 00:01:45.540
This may be due to social expectations.

00:01:45.680 --> 00:01:49.120
However, psychologist Adam Pasteur suggests

00:01:49.140 --> 00:01:54.620
that our attraction to red may be a hangover from humans evolutionary past,

00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:57.800
as animals, such as female baboons,

00:01:57.860 --> 00:02:02.960
display patches of bright red skin to indicate that they are ready to mate.

00:02:03.080 --> 00:02:06.020
Number Eight: Be funny!

00:02:06.120 --> 00:02:10.940
Humor is actually a huge factor in the search of a potential mate.

00:02:10.940 --> 00:02:15.320
University of New Mexico psychologist professor Jeffrey Miller

00:02:15.360 --> 00:02:21.500
